Right. These vehicles are not toys. They are heavy-frame commercial
vehicles. One of the reasons VW pulled the T5 out of the US market is
that they still use the truck frame construction, but they are
competing in price against cheap US made unibody vans. So then they
got the bright idea to compete by letting Chrysler rebrand one of
their vans for them, and the rest is history...

